Oh my jesus. How awesome was HFS? Quite awesome, indeed. So was the christmas shopping trip with Alex & Lauren. Who do you hate Lauren? BRIAN DENNY?!?!?! heh. we're weird. we also hate his bandmates.
HFS Highlights:
-I didn't die.
-Mikey had fun after Breaking Benjamin left. They were horrible. No stage presence what-so-ever.
-Chevelle! omg, me and sam rocked so hard, man. as lame as it sounds, we rocked out with our socks out.
-Crowd surfing is so much fun. i thought i was going to die but i didnt. Jehan and Chris lifted me up once or twice and threw me onto the crowd. It was very invigorating.
- Mosh pits are stupid, pointless,and scary.
-Franz Ferdinand and The Killers were superb! The lead singer of the Killers seemed like a bit of an ass. Eh, he's hot, it's ok.
-Lead singer of Franz is hothothot!!!
-We met these 2 kids, Melanie and Paul. Melanie was the ideal girl for Jehan. Cute, witty, beautiful, and just....perfect. We didnt know how old she was. She was 15. He was soooo sad. She looked like 18. Her brother was 16 and very hot, but J was really down in the dumps today. He said if she were older, he would easily be able to fall in love with someone like that. We forgot to get their phone numbers, too. A terrible thing. I feel really bad for him.
-Good Charlotte is the worst band to ever be created. ewwwww. they were horrible. Chris hit the lead singer with a piece of ice and J hit the bassist. ahahah.
- Jimmy Eat World and My Chemical Romance were pretty good, as well. We missed Keane. I kinda wanted to hear them/him/it/whatever.
-The epitome of good music = Velevet Revolver. Boy can ole Scottie wiggle it!
- My ass got grabbed so many times when we were crowd surfing. heh heh
-Me and Sam both almost hit Chris in the face with our butts. He looked up and thought "hey! i know those asses!". Silly Chris. (Chris & Sam 12-4-04)
-I had a spec-freaking-tacular night and i plan on going to HFS this summer.
